result.execSummary:
The defendant Aaron J. Turcotte was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Strangulation and Suffocation, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.235(1).
  • Bail Jumping-Felony, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).
  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Def's JU,NEJ,NOC to Langlade Co Jail

Defendant Aaron J. Turcotte in court with attorney Brent Harold Debord.  Defendant Aaron J. Turcotte in custody.  Elizabeth R. Constable appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court calls 14CF214, 14CM184, 15CF5 and 16CF145 @ 10:47 a.m. 16CF145 - Waiver of prelim filed. Court reviews with Defendant. Court accepts waiver and finds probable cause. Def bound over. Information filed. Copy received, reading waived, not guilty pleas. Court receives pleas to all counts. Atty Debord will contact public defender office to appoint new counsel. Status conf. 1/30/17 @ 3:30. 14CF214, 14CM184, 15CF5 - sentence after revocation on all, motion to revoke DEJ on ct 1 of 15CF5 and 14CF214. Def not contesting motions. Revocation packets received by parties. No additions or corrections by State. Statement by Atty Debord, no additions. Agreement - 14CF214 ct 1 - 3 yrs prison, 18 months initial, 2 yrs ext supv.  14CM184 - 9 months jail, concurrent, 15CF5 - ct 1 - 6 yrs prison, 3 yrs initial, 3 yrs ext supv. Ct 2 - 3 1/2 yrs prison, 18 months intial,  2yrs ext supv, ct 3 - 90 days jail, concurrent. 14CF214 - credit 186 days, 15CF5 - 244 days credit, 14CM184 - 162 days credit. These sentences to run concurrent to Marathon Co 14CF1079 sentence. Sentencing remarks by Counsel. Statement by Defendant. State has complied with victim rights. Remarks by the Court. Orders - 14CM184 - 9 months jail, credit for 162 days served. Convert outstanding court obligations to civil judgment. 14CF214 ct 1 - 3 1/2 yrs prison, 18 mo initial, 2 yrs ext supv, credit for 186 days served. Ct 2 - 30 days jail, concurrent w/ct 1. All sentences will be concurrent with each other and to Marathon Co case. Ct 3 - 9 months jail, concurrent. Civil judgment for outstanding obligations. 15CF5 ct 1 - 6 yrs prison, 3 yrs initial, 3 yrs ext supv, ct 2 - 3 1/2 yrs prison, 18 months initial, 2 yrs ext supv. Ct 3 - 90 days jail. All concurrent. Credit for 244 days served. Convert outstanding oblig. to civil judgment. Def advised of firearms and voting restrictions. Def eligible for earned release and challenge inc. programs. Postconviction rights. State recommends conditions of ext supv on DEJ cts - pay costs, AODA and follow through, absolute sobriety, no contact with T. B., domestice abuse counseling and any other counseling as recommended by agent. Discussion regarding no contact condition. Court orders ext supv conditions 14CF214 ct 1, 15CF5 ct 1 - court costs. (15CF5 - ct 1 DNA surcharge and sample only if not already on file.)  Counseling as required. No use of alcohol. Court leaves no contact with T.B. to discretion of probation officer. Postconviction rights.  Status conference scheduled for January 30, 2017 at 03:30 pm.
Motion hearing on September 12, 2016 at 03:00 pm.
